<div id="dis1" style="display: none;">
<p>Academic Dismissal permanently restricts a student from attending BYU&ndash;Idaho. Academic Dismissal is a result of performing below the established BYU&ndash;Idaho academic standards after being placed on Academic Suspension. Students who wish to continue a formal education will need to seek opportunities elsewhere.</p>
</div>
<div id="dis2" style="display: none;">
<p>If a student feels there are extenuating circumstances (e.g., health issues, family emergencies, etc.) that affected their ability to do well in school, they may petition their Dismissal through the following steps:</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>Log on to <a href="http://my.byui.edu"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">http://my.byui.edu</span></a></li>
<li>&ldquo;Sign in&rdquo; on the top right-hand side of the page</li>
<li>Select the blue Student or Former Student tab</li>
<li>Select Academic Forms from the gray task bar on the left</li>
<li>Select the Academic Suspension Petition link</li>
</ol>
<p>Students with questions regarding Academic Dismissal can email <a href="mailto:srrpetitions@byui.edu"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">srrpetitions@byui.edu</span></a> or call (208) 496-1042.</p>
</div>
